What does a full-stack developer do?

Career paths

Full-stack developers build and maintain the back-end and front-end aspects of websites or apps. This versatility makes them highly sought after by companies.
A full-stack developer is responsible for both back-end and front-end development. Back-end development involves working on server-side software, while front-end development entails building client-side software.

2. Real industry experience

Towards the end of the web development bootcamp, students are grouped under teams to implement coding projects for a real company. Our career team filters projects to make sure that they are interesting and provide a tangible benefit to the client.

Each student tests a part of the broader project with the final goal of delivering a detailed bug report to the client. The idea is to replicate a professional environment where web developers write code, test the results, and provide detailed reports about their work. We replicate a remote working environment complete with a team lead, Agile sprints, and task tickets.

The project ends with each student making a final presentation about their work.

3. Career Prep Course

One-on-one coaching will help take your website development job search to the next level. Our career coaches are experienced HR and recruiting professionals with years in the industry. They'll help you work on your professional self-presentation, develop a job search strategy, and refine your approach for better results. You'll know exactly which jobs to apply for and the best way to apply for them.
Career coaches and tech industry leads will take you through a series of mock interviews. Ever wonder why HR folks ask the questions they do or whether you can provide the right answers to these questions? Our career coaches will give you that knowledge and feedback.

We'll also prep you for technical interviews — you'll go through typical interview tasks and scenarios and learn how to approach them.
Your TripleTen projects will be professionally reviewed line-by-line, while your externship project will receive feedback from our employer partners. Because TripleTen teaches the best web development practices, you’ll stand out in a crowded tech field.
Learn how to write a compelling resume and cover letter. Our career coaches know what recruiters, automated recruiting systems, and HR folks look for. They’ll happily save you the hours of tinkering and doubt that resumes frequently face.
